rComments: This was one of the most educational classes i've taken here. The quizes and tests are HARD though.

Chambers is a great professor and knows an abundant amount of information on the subject.  The quiz and test graders are VERY picky and it is literally impossible to get perfect grades.  The project is tons of work, but a great experience.  i would only recommend this class if you are prepared to work and you are passionate about advertising.

He is a good scholar, not a good professor.  He's very knowledgeable on the subject but doesn't give a damn about his students. He grades very harshly and nitpicks the most inconsequential of details. He cares more about his reputation than the class.

I loved Dr. Chambers! I never thought advertising history could be at all interesting but he definitely can keep your attention! Hard class though... a LOT of reading, but I would still recommend it as an Advertising elective.
Jason Chambers is one hot man!  he is basically a ****.  I enjoyed his pocket squares and random hats.  this class is really interesting, but you HAVE to read the books.  his tests are ridiculous.
There is a ridiculous amount of reading and the graders of the quizzes and tests are anal. The project was not bad but i would not recommend this class.
